            <p class="text-justify">I obtained my BSc in Chemistry (<time datetime="2011">2011</time>) and MSc in Theoretical and Computational Chemistry (<time datetime="2012">2012</time>) at the <a href="https://www.urv.cat/en/">Rovira i Virgili University</a> (Spain). In <time datetime="2012">2012</time>, I joined the <a href="http://rodi.urv.es/w3qf/index.html">Quantum Chemistry Group</a> at the Department of Physical Chemistry and Inorganics at Rovira i Virgili University, where I received a PhD. fellowship (<time datetime="2012">2012</time>-<time datetime="2016">2016</time>) under the supervision of <a href="https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0322-6796">Dr. X. López</a>, <a href="https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5884-5629">Dr. A. Rodríguez-Fortea</a> and <a href="https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4533-0623">Prof. Josep M. Poblet</a>. During the PhD, I participated in projects funded by Spanish State Agency and the European Comission (COST) and I was awarded with two mobility grants to visit Newcastle University.</p>
            <p class="text-justify">My PhD thesis was based mainly in computational chemistry. As part of my thesis, I studied the reactivity and NMR characterization of Polyoxometalates, from both the computational and experimental point of view. In order to extent my education in this topic, in <time datetime="2013">2013</time> I was invited for a 3-month stay at the experimental group lead by <a href="https://www.ncl.ac.uk/nes/staff/profile/johnerrington.html">Dr. R. John Errington</a>, at Newcastle University (UK). I did a second stay at Newcastle University in April <time datetime="2016">2016</time>. I defended my PhD thesis entitled <a href="http://hdl.handle.net/10803/440510">"Computational Modelling of Polyoxometalates: Progress on the Accurate NMR Characterization and Reactivity"</a> <time datetime="2017-03">March 2017</time>. During the last year of my PhD studies (<time datetime="2017">2017</time>), I also completed my master's degree in Education (<time datetime="2017">2017</time>).</p>
            <p class="text-justify">After my PhD, I was honoured with a competitive Postdoctoral position at <a href="https://www.umu.se/en/">Umeå University</a> (Sweden) at the <a href="http://moleculargeo.chem.umu.se/en/">Molecular Geochemistry Laboratory</a>. The project was focused on NMR spectroscopy and equilibrium studies of complex molecules and computational modelling of metal oxide in solution.</p>
            <p class="text-justify">In <time datetime="2019">2019</time>, I started working as Postdoctoral Research Associate as part of the EPSRC-JSPS Core-to-Core International Network on "Polyoxometalate Science for Advanced Functional Energy Materials" at <a href="https://www.ncl.ac.uk/">Newcastle University</a> (UK). The project is based on Polyoxometalates as candidates for energy storage applications.</p>

